race.comment: Exciting 3YO HEEZA PHOENIX (6) looks to punch his ticket to Flemington. He's fresh here off 63 days but did have a racecourse gallop here last week. Has the speed to roll across from out wide and it's easy to think there's still improvement to come. Short of his best trip, but may just be too classy. PROSPECTOR'S PICK (7) got back to winning ways last start when scoring by 0.4L at this track and trip. He steps back up in grade, but he's much better suited at 1200m and CJP sticks with him. Needs some luck from the draw, but can repeat the dose if luck comes his way. RICHANCO (1) comes back from the Miss Andretti where he wasn't beaten far. Blinkers go on first time today and the claim of Nottle comes in handy. Ticks a few boxes and a forward showing is expected. ELITE MISSILE (3) boasts a strong fresh record and looks forward enough to run well fresh. LET'S TALK (10) rates highly on the last start win and can make his presence felt in this tougher company.
